# Code of Conduct

To maintain a welcoming, productive community, all contributors are expected to follow this Code of Conduct.

## Our Standards

Examples of positive behavior:
- Being respectful and constructive
- Offering helpful feedback
- Welcoming new contributors
- Staying on topic in discussions
- Keeping communication clear and professional

Examples of unacceptable behavior:
- Harassment or personal attacks
- Discriminatory comments
- Publishing private information
- Spam or irrelevant self-promotion
- Aggressive or abusive language

## Enforcement

Project maintainers may take appropriate action including warnings, issue locking, or banning users from the repository if violations occur.

## Reporting

If you notice behavior that violates this Code of Conduct,
please open an issue or contact the maintainers directly.
